node.text: The Offset sofa is the result of a research into ‘balance.’ We experimented with offsetting and played with proportions to let the narrow armrests meet the thick generous seat supported by four stubby legs. The new edition with loose covers now introduces an increased longevity, functionality, and versatility to the collection, with its changeable exterior crafted from a custom-made cotton and linen blend textile. Designed for @menuspace. Photography by @jonasbjerrepoulsen #softminimalism #normarchitects

node.text: With the new Cask collection for @expormim, we have scrutinized the various ways that natural rattan can be used to strike a balance between creative ideas and technical realization; The basic structure of the sophisticated lounge chair is created from nothing more than two rounded pieces of rattan connected with vertical sticks and combined with a comfortable upholstery for a cozy and relaxed design exuding a timeless simplicity. Photography by @jonasbjerrepoulsen #softminimalism #normarchitects

node.text: “In creating spaces, timelessness is achieved through a coherence in composition: the spatial features of a space and the forms and elements present in that space. Hence, we need to understand the importance of the dynamic, unseen matter defined by form; how designing objects for a room not only affects the user’s perception of the given object, but of the room itself and of the space left around it.” Photography by @jonasbjerrepoulsen

node.text: Inspired by Japanese and Scandinavian minimalism, the Koku tables master the art of balance, combining light and elegant elements with a certain heaviness. The slender steel tube graciously supports the tabletop and provides contrast to the tactile wooden construction, creating a stimulating and distinctive expression. Designed for @fogiacollection Photography by @jonasbjerrepoulsen #softminimalism #normarchitects

node.text: Art direction and photography for Dinesen in collaboration with Pernille Vest. The collection of interior design objects and furniture stimulates the senses through aesthetic sustainability and is designed to last for generations – only growing more beautiful as time leaves its imprint on the natural materials. Photography by @jonasbjerrepoulsen styling by @pernille.vest #softminimalism #normarchitects @dinesen

node.text: The Kojima Table/Floor lamps, with their wooden base and Washi paper lampshade, almost become a hybrid between a furniture piece and a lamp. A sculptural yet functional lamp, shining a natural, warm non-directional light to the surrounding space. Produced by @kojima_shouten in collaboration with @karimokucasestudy. #normarchitects #softminimalism

node.text: Introducing the recently finished co-living & co-working space @siljangade, Copenhagen. Welcoming all aspects of everyday life, the shared working areas inspire creative sessions and networking in a warm atmosphere, while the smaller studios are fit to embrace a tranquil homelife, private office spaces or maybe even both. Staying at Siljangade means having everything you need just around the corner. Designed for NREP. Photography by @fixiekarl. #normarchitects #softminimalism

node.text: “With the use of stone, dark wood and textured textiles, the interior plays on inspiration from mid-century American Modernism. The living areas with a small bar niche, the open plan kitchen, lush carpets and bulky comfortable furniture draws inspiration from an array of elements – from the Japanese inspired Schindler House in Los Angles to the extravagant New York apartments featured in the series Mad Men” — @frederikwerner, Norm Architects. Designed for @karimokucasestudy. #normarchitects #softminimalism

node.text: Our approach to interior architecture, minimal aesthetics and materiality has been gracefully translated and applied to the yacht settings and restrictions of the 70 foot Y/Yachts model Y7, bringing out a warm and exclusive feel through tactile surfaces, natural materials and matte finishes. The craftsmanship of the walls, panels, lightning, detailing and furnishing beautifully harmonize in the high-performance luxury yacht. Designed for @yyachts_by_michael_schmidt. #normarchitects #yachtbau #softminimalism

node.text: The Village School House, situated north of Copenhagen, lies nestled between unspoiled forests, lakes, and the ocean. Dating back to 1721, the timbered house presents a historic glimpse of traditional Danish architecture. It has been carefully and respectfully renovated, largely preserving the exterior while the interior has been delicately modernised, true to Norm’s guiding principle of finding balance in design, uniting old and new in a thoughtful manner. Image by @jonasbjerrepoulsen. #normarchitects #softminimalism

node.text:
Beosound Stage, the result of our latest collaboration with Bang & Olufsen, is a simple yet elegant soundbar with clean geometric shapes and natural materials to create a product that beautifully integrates into the home. The frame is made from a single piece of forged aluminium, resulting in no visible seams. 

Designed for @bangolufsen. Image by @jonasbjerrepoulsen. #normarchitects #softminimalism
